# üîØ projgeom-py

Projective Geometry in Python

This is a Python conversion of the original Rust [projgeom-rs](https://github.com/luk036/projgeom-rs) library.

## üõ†Ô∏è Installation

### üì¶ pip

```bash
pip install projgeom-py
```

### üì¶ Development Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/luk036/projgeom-rs.git
cd projgeom-rs/python_ai
pip install -e ".[dev]"
```

## üìú Usage

### Basic Projective Geometry

```python
from projgeom import PgPoint, PgLine

# Create points and lines
p1 = PgPoint([1, 2, 3])
p2 = PgPoint([4, 5, 6])
l1 = PgLine([1, 1, -1])

# Check incidence
assert p1.incident(l1) == l1.incident(p1)

# Join two points to get a line
line = p1.meet(p2)
assert line.incident(p1) and line.incident(p2)

# Parametrize between points
mid = p1.parametrize(1, p2, 1)
```

### Euclidean Geometry

```python
from projgeom import EuclidPoint, EuclidLine

# Create Euclidean objects
p = EuclidPoint([1, 2, 1])  # Point (1,2)
l = EuclidLine([1, 0, -1])  # Line x = 1

# Check parallelism and perpendicularity
l1 = EuclidLine([1, 0, -1])  # x = 1
l2 = EuclidLine([2, 0, -5])  # x = 2.5 (parallel to l1)
assert l1.is_parallel(l2)

l3 = EuclidLine([0, 1, -1])  # y = 1
assert l1.is_perpendicular(l3)

# Calculate midpoint
p1 = EuclidPoint([0, 0, 1])
p2 = EuclidPoint([2, 4, 1])
mid = p1.midpoint(p2)  # (1,2)
```

### Cayley-Klein Geometries

```python
from projgeom import (
    HyperbolicPoint, HyperbolicLine,
    EllipticPoint, EllipticLine,
    orthocenter, altitude, reflect
)

# Create a triangle
a = HyperbolicPoint([13, 23, 32])
b = HyperbolicPoint([44, -34, 2])
c = HyperbolicPoint([-2, 12, 23])
triangle = [a, b, c]

# Calculate orthocenter
h = orthocenter(triangle)

# Calculate altitude
alt = altitude(a, b.meet(c))

# Reflect a point
mirror = HyperbolicLine([1, 0, -1])
reflected = reflect(mirror, a)
```

